There are separate stories about it. Discovering tea in China is connected to a half-mythical 

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.990
and legendary first Chinese emperor called Shenong.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:38.000
Since he had divine powers, he decided to discover the effects of all herbs that he had close at hand for people in China.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.990
He wanted to do it to say which ones were healing, which poisonous,

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:49.990
what effect they had and he started to test them. It turned out he came across a harmful plant

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:56.000
that poisoned him and he decided to take a rest, drink some water and fight the toxins inside him,

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:03.000
so he chose a big tree, put some fire and kettle under it to heat water because he drank cooked water for health.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:09.990
He decided to rest there. While waiting for water to boil, he fell asleep

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:14.990
and it turned out in the meantime a leaf fell from the tree and got into the kettle.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:21.000
It steeped and it was a tea leaf, indeed. When Shenong woke up he saw that the aromatic brew in his kettle looks and smells lovely.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:29.990
He drank it and it turned out his fatigue was gone. It also made him refreshed and energized

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:34.990
and all the symptoms connected with the poisoning by harmful plant disappeared.

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:37.990
This was how Shenong discovered tea and its wonderful healing properties.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:43.990
He contributed to it healing properties that cured all the diseases and poisonings.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:50.000
Later while testing other herbs, after tasting every single herb that he wasn't sure of,

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:57.000
Shenong drank the healing tea at any case and that's how tea was approved in China as a very healthy healing brew.

