Beginnings of tea in Japan are related to Bodhidharm, a Buddhist monk from India

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:12.000
got to Japan through China where he set up a Buddhist fraction called Zen and started to introduce Zen philosophy

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:20.000
which is tightly connected with tea. Where does it come from? Well, Bodhidharm, as a typical Buddhist monk, meditated a lot

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:26.990
and he often fell asleep during allnight meditations. He had a problem with it, fell asleep, 

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.990
and one day he was so angry with his eyelids that they drop down during his meditation

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:35.990
that with a burst of frustration he decided to pull them away, 

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:39.990
or cut them off as another version says. He threw them behind him.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.990
Thanks to that his eyes no longer closed and he could meditate all night long.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:48.990
In the morning it turned out that a bush grew out of his eyelids behind his back.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:55.000
